{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_32","type":"reasoning","text":"**Updating test harness**\n\nIŌĆÖm considering whether to update the test harness for the wrapper path to keep it consistent with the head-base helper. It might be good to create a new test file that references existing Python functions to verify parity. ThereŌĆÖs code change involved, and it could relate to IQ-150, even if it isnŌĆÖt strictly necessary. IŌĆÖm thinking of modifying existing tests and possibly emulating the wrapper allocation path, but itŌĆÖs a C function without a direct Python equivalent.\n**Creating new validation function**\n\nI'm thinking of creating a simple function in Python called `rope_q16_rotate_head_range_by_token_window_preflighted_execution_checked`. It would allocate a cache list and call the `head_bases` checked from another test module. Then, I could compare its results with the existing `preflighted_checked` function for various randomized and edge cases. This seems like a great way to enhance validation. I should also inspect the existing `token_window.py` to see what functions like `run` it has."}}
